    excerpt: "Falls are the leading cause of injury and disability in adults over 60. The right orthotic support can dramatically reduce fall risk and help maintain independence in older age.",
    content: `In India, over 100 million people are aged 60 or above — and falls are the single greatest preventable cause of disability in this group. More than 30% of adults over 65 fall each year. Hip fractures from falls carry a one-year mortality rate of up to 30%.

Orthotics for older adults is a specialised field at ${CLINIC}. We understand that an elderly patient has different priorities, different physiology, and different emotional needs than a younger patient.

## Why Older Adults Are at Higher Risk of Falls

- **Reduced proprioception** — Less feedback from the feet about ground surface
- **Muscle weakness** — Sarcopenia (age-related muscle loss) affects balance and stability
- **Arthritis** — Joint pain changes gait pattern, reducing stability
- **Reduced vision** — Contributes to spatial disorientation
- **Polypharmacy** — Multiple medications often cause dizziness
- **Foot deformities** — Bunions, hammer toes, and flat arches develop with age

## Orthotic Solutions for Older Adults

**AFO for Post-Stroke Foot Drop**
Stroke is common in older adults. Post-stroke foot drop is effectively managed with a lightweight AFO. We design specifically for frail elderly skin — using softer materials, well-padded edges, and easy Velcro fastening.

**KAFO / Caliper for Post-Polio Syndrome**
Many adults in Lucknow and Uttar Pradesh had polio in childhood. In older age, post-polio syndrome causes new-onset muscle weakness. A KAFO (also known as a caliper) can restore safe, independent walking.

**Knee Orthosis for Osteoarthritis**
Osteoarthritis of the knee affects over 40% of adults over 65. An unloader knee brace or patellofemoral support can reduce pain, improve stability, and delay the need for surgical intervention.

**Custom Foot Orthoses (Insoles)**
For flat feet, plantar fasciitis, and arthritic foot pain. Custom insoles redistribute pressure, reduce pain, and improve walking confidence.

## Home Visits in Lucknow

We offer home visits for elderly or severely mobility-impaired patients in Lucknow and surrounding areas. Ask about this service when you contact us.

## Key Message for Families

If your elderly parent or grandparent is walking less steadily, experiencing knee or back pain, or has recently had a fall — please do not wait. Early orthotic intervention, combined with physiotherapy and appropriate footwear, can meaningfully extend functional independence.`
